# Tools

Collection of utility tools for blockchain development and interaction.

## utf8-sender.html

Simple browser-based tool for sending UTF-8 text messages directly to Ethereum blockchain via transaction data.

### Features
- Send any UTF-8 text as blockchain transaction data
- MetaMask integration for wallet connectivity
- Sepolia testnet support
- Real-time gas estimation
- No external dependencies beyond MetaMask

### Use Cases
- Testing blockchain messaging systems
- Proof-of-concept for on-chain communication
- Debugging transaction data handling
- Educational demonstrations of blockchain data storage

### Usage
1. Open `utf8-sender.html` in any modern browser
2. Connect MetaMask wallet
3. Enter recipient address and message text
4. Send transaction

### Technical Details
- Uses native browser TextEncoder for proper UTF-8 encoding
- Converts text to hex format for transaction data field
- Supports emoji and special characters
- Transaction data is publicly readable on blockchain explorers

### Requirements
- MetaMask browser extension
- Sepolia testnet ETH for gas fees
- Modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)

---

*Note: All transaction data on public blockchains is permanently visible. Never include sensitive information in messages.*